        <h3>What are computers?</h3>
        <p><strong>What they are:</strong> Computers are electronic machines that receive, process, and store information.</p>
        <p><strong>What they’re for:</strong> They help people perform many tasks, such as writing, calculating, communicating, and accessing the internet.</p>

        <h3>How do they work?</h3>
        <p><strong>How they work:</strong> Computers work by following instructions called programs. These instructions tell the computer what actions to perform.</p>
        <p><strong>Process:</strong> The computer receives input, processes the data using its hardware and software, and produces an output.</p>

        <h3>What is the most important part?</h3>
        <p><strong>The most important part:</strong> The CPU (Central Processing Unit) acts like the “brain” of the computer.</p>
